MARINE BIVALVES & PUBLIC HEALTH - ARGENTINA: REQUEST
FOR INFO
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Mon, 23 Aug 1999 18:06:42 -0300
From: Sergio Sosa Estani <ssosaestani@abaconet.com.ar>

Several beaches in Argentina have been invaded by _Limnoperma
fortunei_. I would like confirm that this invasion is not a public health
problem.
I would be grateful to receive information about whether this bivalve
can transmit microorganisms such as trematodes or others.
